  {
    "type": "EXEGETICAL (ORIGINAL LANGUAGES)",
    "name": "Pulpit Commentary",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cmt_sub_title",
        "text": "Verse 20.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " - ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cmt_word",
        "text": "Candlesticks... lamps, that they should burn after the manner before the oracle.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " Ten candlesticks, as we learn here and in ver. 7, supersede in Solomon's temple the ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "accented",
        "text": "one",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " candlestick, with its central shaft lamp, and the three branch lamps on either side of Moses and the tabernacle (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Exodus 25:31-37",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Exodus 37:17-24",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Leviticus 24:4",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "; Josephus, 'Ant.,' 3:06. § 6, 7; Maimonides [1135-1205], \"De temple, vasis sanctuarii,\" etc.). This single candlestick was restored in Zerubbabel's temple. The present ten ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "accented",
        "text": "candlesticks",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", or strictly candelabra, of Solomon are said at one time to have been placed in a row like a rail before the veil, and connected with a chain under which the high priest went on the Day of Atonement into the inner sanctuary. The removal of these candelabra is recorded ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Jeremiah 52:19",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". The expression, \"after the manner,\" points to the various and somewhat minute regulation for the lighting, trimming, and keeping alight of the ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "accented",
        "text": "lamps",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", all or some, of the candelabra (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Exodus 27:19-21",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Leviticus 24:1-3",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "). The use of the word for \"lamp\" (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "hebrew",
        "text": "נֵר",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ") in some passages (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "1 Samuel 3:3",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "2 Samuel 21:17",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Proverbs 13:9",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Proverbs 20:27",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Psalm 18:29",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ")suggests not the part as used for the whole in speaking of the candelabrum, but more probably that the ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "accented",
        "text": "perpetual",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " burning was not of all seven lamps, but of one, the central shaft. 2 Chronicles 4:20",
        "children": []
      },
